Section 1:
Act 688 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1824
4
5 By: Representatives Duffield, Beaty Jr., M. Brown, A. Collins, Crawford, Ennett, D. Garner, Gazaway,
6 Gonzales Worthen, Hollowell, Hudson, McCullough, J. Moore, Pearce, T. Shephard, Tosh, Unger, D.
7 Whitaker, Wooten
8 By: Senators A. Clark, C. Tucker
9
For An Act To Be Entitled
10
11 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING CRUELTY TO
12 ANIMALS; TO CREATE THE DOG AND CAT RESCUE ACT:
13 DAISY'S LAW; TO AUTHORIZE LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICERS TO
14 SECURE A DOG OR CAT IN CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES; AND FOR
15 OTHER PURPOSES.
16
17
Subtitle
18
19 TO CREATE THE DOG AND CAT RESCUE ACT:
20 DAISY'S LAW.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Title.
25 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Dog and Cat Rescue
26 Act: Daisy's Law".
27
28 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 5, Chapter 62, Subchapter 1, is amended
29 to add an additional section to read as follows:
30 5-62-128. Law enforcement securing dogs and cats.
31 (a) In addition to the disposition of a dog or cat provided under ยง 5-
32 62-106, following a complaint of cruelty to dogs or cats under this
33 subchapter, a law enforcement officer may temporarily secure a dog or cat and
34 transfer temporary possession of the dog or cat to an appropriate place of
35 custody if a substantial likelihood exists that the condition of the dog or
36 cat would deteriorate if the dog or cat was not secured by the law
*CRH098*
03/17/2025 3:38:57 PM CRH098
HB1824
1 enforcement officer.
2 (b) A law enforcement officer may use the condition or the securing of
3 other dogs or cats belonging to the same owner as evidence to support
4 securing the dog or cat under subsection (a) of this section.
